column2: lake is nicer than I've seen it before in mid-June; 200 ml filtered for chl
clear- slight wind from SW- 70 degrees- tiny green algal colonies in water- lot of EWM and curly-leaf pondweed in  boat landing bay; no hydrogen sulfide smell at dam
storm 1-3/4 inches of rain in 15 minutes on 5/2/06- also rain on 5/28 and 5/30
Scattered clouds- slight wind- lots of floating + decaying pieces of milfoil- coontail- curly-leaf turions- filamentous algae- and other debris.  Small plankton algae bloom.
slight breeze; less floating plants/algae than 2 weeks ago; bottom water just slight musty- H2SO4 smell; small phytoplankton (not nuisance blue-greens); NO ambient H2SO4 smeel from downstream of dam
Floating plant fragments - mostly coontail + EWM; skies clear- wind SE 15 mph; NO floating globs of blue-green Oscillatoria like Cox Hollow; NO ambient hydrogen sulfide smell as in previous years.
Cloudy- wind from E at 8 mph- 55- tiny round green colonies in water
75. overcast- slight breeze- 1.7" rain + high winds in last few days- small green algae suspended in water- not a lot of zooplankton- large fish on sonar at 14-29"
Clear to partly cloudy- 80- slight breeze- duckweed on surface thoughout lake- some floating clumps of plants- round green algae colonies in water.
Calm- overcast- 80- humid- more than 5 inches of rain sine 8/4- more than 3 inches of rain since; blue-green algae bloom- small round colonies- floating- decaying EWM- around 30 canoers.
Calm- partly cloudy- humid- 73 degrees- heavy rain previous day- assisted by Donna Sefton and Bill Upton
Overcast-75 degrees- rained earlier in day- young bald eagle present
Sunny- breezy- 2 geese- 2 coots- 2 wooducks- 1 loon
Mostly cloudy- 75 degrees F- heavy rain previous day
Sunny- 1 hen turkey- 4 geese and 21 painted turtles
